	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99824945070303><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=99824945070303>RE: Research?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=99824945070303#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Aug 19th 3:30 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Good question I am lvl 16 and for a long time was confused about what research was but now i know.<br><br>Ok when you hit lvl 16 you can do research which will be used later in the game to create spells that you cannot buy from vendors (ie higher lvl pet spells).&nbsp;&nbsp;You need two things to be a researcher.<br><br>1.  Concordance of research:  This is a book that is a container with a combine button much like brewing and other containers.  You can get this by doing a quest.  To do this quest is easy.  Either buy or keep killing Willow-Wisps untill you get a Greater Lightstone.  Next step is to take your GLightstone to your appr research Trainor.  If you are good there is North Karana goto the Gypsy Camp and give it to one of the Gypsys (not sure of her name).  If you are an evil race travel to Southern Ro and see the female DE at loc (200, 500 near tents ?).<br>I was a gnome and wanted my concordance when I was like lvl 7 (lol) and in order to get it I had to get to NKarana which means going through High Pass Hold (I has to tele's peeps where not generous).  So I thought to myself let me try the evil NPC in SRO because the desert is open ground to run and only 2 zones away from efreeport.  So after a couple times getting killed in SRO I got camoflauge (I still didnt have invisi hehe) and made it to her gave her the GLightstonne and the biatch said I dont help out your kind (urrrr).  So I got another GLightsonte from a friend gave it to my DE friend and had him get it for me so I had the concordance of research at lvl 7.<br><br>2.  Elemental Grimoire:  Another book that acts like a combine container.  There is a quest for this but I just bought it in WFree.<br><br>Ok now you know that research is a way to create spell scrolls without having to purchase them.  You will use the Elemental Grimoire book to make the spells (ie lvl 16 water pet you put shark skin, lvl 12 water pet scroll, word of tyranny, quill (pen), and parchment and combine to get your lvl 16 water pet inside the grimoire).<br><br>Now your prob asking what is the Concordance of research for.  PRACTICE, making your skill better.  When you gain lvls you are aloud to put 5 more points to ie abj, conj if you max yourself out every lvl which I do.  You do this by casting summon food (etc) until your conj is maxed right.  Well  you need to create practice runes to up your research lvl.  When you first hit 16 goto the mage guild and just train 1 pt in research (you can only do that much anyway until lvl 19).  I am not going to go into how to make practice runes (see link below) but you will make an azia rune by putting azia components into the concordance and combining and breza by putting components in concordance and combining.  You will ALWAYS BE SUCCESSFUL at creating the practice runes (I have 10 made sitting in the bank till lvl 19) its taking BOTH AZIA and BREZA and putting them in your GRIMOIRE and combining them that raises your Research skill and just like brewing and other skills you may gain a lvl and you just may loose the runes.  Now there are different lvls of Practice Runes that gor trivial meaning once you reach that level you cant gain more levels from those types of runes.  Go here for a listing of components for each level of practice rune:  <br><br><a href="http://mythiran.allakhazam.com/practice_walkthru.html" target=_new>http://mythiran.allakhazam.com/practice_walkthru.html</a><br><br>Go here for a listing of spells that can be researched:<br><br><a href="http://mythiran.allakhazam.com/mage.html" target=_new>http://mythiran.allakhazam.com/mage.html</a><br><br>Finally my last word is practice as much as you can because if you havent put either training points from the 5 per level or from old fashioned making of practice runes and you get to hgiher levels where you have to go around the world getting components and you finally have what you need to make your say eg lvl 40 water pet spell which just for arguments sake cannot be bought and you put the 3 components into the GRIMOIRE and you hit combine and it tells you you failed to make it because your to DUMB in research then you just wasted sweat and blood and money.<br><br>Hope this helps<br><br>Seriallova<br>lvl 16 Mage<br>Erollisi Marr<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
