	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Aug 21st 10:43 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well, you get the line of 'shielding' spells which lets you increase your HP and AC. Later on(starting at level 8) you get damage sheilds. Damage shields can be cast on anyone, and they make it so that whenever the person with the damage shield is hit, the thing that hit them, takes an amount of damage. The damage shields also increase your fire resistance. Starting at level 16 you get the phantom armor buffs, which let you increase your own AC. The phantom armor buffs also let you regain hitpoints faster. Starting at level 12 you get a line of buffs called the 'burnout' series which can only be cast on your pet. The burnout series makes your pets dish out more damage. Thats pretty much it. Magicians don't get many buffs that can be cast on other players.<br><br>Former EQ Addict.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
